statement.title: Problem Description
statement.content: There are N players playing a guessing game. Each player guesses a sequence consists of {1,2,3,4,5,6} with length L, then a dice will be rolled again and again and the roll out sequence will be recorded. The player whose guessing sequence first matches the last L rolls of the dice wins the game.

statement.title: Input
statement.content: The first line is the number of test cases. For each test case, the first line contains 2 integers N (1 ≤ N ≤ 10) and L (1 ≤ L ≤ 10). Each of the following N lines contains a guessing sequence with length L. It is guaranteed that the guessing sequences are consist of {1,2,3,4,5,6} and all the guessing sequences are distinct.

statement.title: Output
statement.content: For each test case, output a line containing the winning probability of each player with the precision of 6 digits.
